Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water with a
good pinch of @salt{} on to boil for the potato. Peel the @baking potato{1}
and chop into 1cm thick slices. Trim the root and the dark green leafy part
from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice widthways. Thinly
slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}. Pick the @thyme{1/2%sprig} leaves
from their stalks (discard the stalks).

Add the potato to your pan of boiling water. Cook for ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through. Be
> careful - you don't want the potato slices to break up too much!

Once cooked, gently drain your potato slices in a #colander{}.

Put a splash of @olive oil{1} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Throw
in the leek. Cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Add the mushrooms and thyme
along with a pinch of salt and a grind of @black pepper{}. Stir together
and cook for another ~{7%minutes}.

Once the mushrooms have softened pour in the @water{100ml}. Add the
@vegetable stock powder{1/2%pot}, bring to the boil and stir to dissolve.
Add the @creme fraiche{150%g}. Turn the heat to low and simmer for
~{3-5%minutes}. Add the @chopped kale{100%g} and stir to wilt the leaves.
Continue to simmer gently until the liquid has reduced by a third,
another ~{5%minutes}. Take the pan off the heat.

Meanwhile, mix the @panko breadcrumbs{30%g} with the olive oil in a
#mixing bowl{}. Crumble in the @feta cheese{100%g} and stir well.

Once cooked, pour the veggie mixture into an #ovenproof dish{}. Lay your
potato slices on top, then sprinkle over the feta crumb and season
with black pepper. Pop on the top shelf of your oven and bake until
the top is browned, ~{10%minutes}. Once your pie is ready, remove it
from the oven and serve in #bowls{}. Enjoy!

> Now you have dished up your meal, take a moment to reflect and feel proud
> of what you have made. Make sure you take the time to congratulate yourself
> before the first bite. Enjoy!